On the coast again are Antandros previously called Edonis, then Cimmeris, and Assos, which is the same as Apollonia3 and formerly there was also the town of Palamedium. Then Cape Lectum which marks the frontier between the Aeolid and the Tr0ad3 also there was once the city—state of Polymedia, and Chrysa and another Larisa : the temple of Zmintheus still stands. Colone inland has disappeared. Adramytteos is resorted to for legal business by the people of Apollonia on the river Rhyndacus, the Eresi, Miletopolitae, Poemaneni, Macedonian Asculacae, Polichnaei, Pionitae, the Cilician Man- dacandeni, the Mysian peoples known as the Abret- teni and the Hellespontii, and others of no note.
